# Research Use Only License

Copyright (c) 2026 Scott Thornton

## Permitted Uses

This security research and its materials may be used for:

✅ **Defensive Security Research** - Studying vulnerabilities to build better protections
✅ **Educational Purposes** - Learning about AI security threats and defenses
✅ **Security Tool Development** - Creating detection and mitigation systems
✅ **Academic Study** - Citing methodology and findings in research papers
✅ **Internal Security Testing** - Testing your own authorized systems

## Prohibited Uses

This research may NOT be used for:

❌ **Malicious Attacks** - Attacking systems you don't own or have authorization to test
❌ **Weaponization** - Creating automated exploitation tools for widespread use
❌ **Unauthorized Testing** - Bypassing security without explicit permission
❌ **Illegal Activities** - Any use that violates applicable laws or regulations
❌ **Unethical Purposes** - Causing harm to systems, users, or organizations

## Responsible Disclosure

This research follows responsible disclosure principles:

- **Methodology Shared** - Attack patterns and defense strategies explained conceptually
- **Working Exploits Not Included** - No exact prompts or automated attack code provided
- **Defense-Focused** - Every vulnerability includes corresponding mitigation approaches
- **Ethical Standards** - Research conducted in authorized environments only

## Disclaimer

THIS RESEARCH IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. THE AUTHOR ASSUMES NO RESPONSIBILITY FOR MISUSE OF THIS INFORMATION OR ANY DAMAGES RESULTING FROM ITS USE.

Security researchers using this work must:
1. Obtain proper authorization before testing any systems
2. Follow ethical disclosure practices
3. Prioritize defense development over exploitation
4. Comply with all applicable laws and regulations

## Attribution

When citing this research, please use:

**APA Format:**
```
Thornton, S. (2025). Chain-of-Thought Jailbreak Research: When AI Reasoning
Becomes the Attack Surface. GitHub Repository.
https://github.com/[your-username]/cot-jailbreak-research-public
```

**IEEE Format:**
```
S. Thornton, "Chain-of-Thought Jailbreak Research: When AI Reasoning Becomes
the Attack Surface," GitHub Repository, Nov. 2025. [Online].
Available: https://github.com/[your-username]/cot-jailbreak-research-public
